scopecontent.p:
"I have not sent the drawing to Mr Richmonds because I can't bear to send it about till it is framed -- the surface is so delicate. I will get it framed ... I have kept your sketches -- I have no doubt you can easily have them when you come to town -- I am very busy -- bothered with woodcuts for my book for beginners [
                        The Elements of Drawing
                     ] -- doing them in a hurry -- the etching having got spoiled in biting." [Date provided by Surtees: ? April 1857]
